---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Overfitting Safeguards">
  <h1>Overfitting Safeguards</h1>

  <p>Agent Forge includes multiple layers to prevent agents from optimizing to pass a narrow test suite instead of serving the intended use case (Goodhart's Law).</p>

  <h2>The Problem</h2>
  <blockquote>
    <p>When a measure becomes a target, it ceases to be a good measure.</p>
    <p>— Goodhart's Law</p>
  </blockquote>
  <p>If the TestGenerator creates 5 nearly identical test cases about null pointers, the agent can "pass" without learning to detect race conditions, style violations, or any other aspect of the real use case.</p>

  <h2>Safeguard Layers</h2>

  <h3>1. Diversity Enforcement (TestGenerator)</h3>
  <p>After generating <code>k</code> test cases, pairwise Jaccard similarity is computed on inputs. Any test with similarity greater than 0.7 to an existing test is rejected and regenerated.</p>
  <pre><code>function jaccardSimilarity(a, b):
  aStr = JSON.stringify(a)
  bStr = JSON.stringify(b)
  if aStr equals bStr: return 1
  // compute intersection over union
  return intersection / union</code></pre>

  <h3>2. Intent Tracing (TestGenerator)</h3>
  <p>Every test case includes a <code>tracedTo</code> field mapping it to clauses in the original NL description. After test generation, <code>checkCoverage()</code> identifies any aspect of the description with zero test coverage. If "style violations" has no tests, a coverage gap is flagged.</p>

  <h3>3. Coverage Completeness (QualityGate)</h3>
  <p>If any aspect of the original intent has no test coverage:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>A <code>coverageGaps</code> alert is added to the ScoreReport</li>
    <li><code>QualityGate</code> sets blocked to true</li>
    <li>Export is halted until gaps are resolved</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>4. Generalization Holdout (Evaluator)</h3>
  <p>After an agent passes all generated tests, 3 shadow test cases are run against it. These are:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Within the intended scope of the agent</li>
    <li>Not similar to any training test case</li>
    <li>Used only to check whether the agent generalizes or memorizes</li>
  </ul>
  <p>If generalization score less than 0.5, a warning is attached to the agent record. The agent still passes, but the warning persists.</p>

  <h3>5. Audit Trail (Registry)</h3>
  <p>Every agent version stores:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Which test cases it was trained on</li>
    <li>Which test cases it was evaluated against</li>
    <li>Full failure reports per iteration</li>
  </ul>
  <p>This makes it possible to trace back: "Why did v3 pass but v4 fail?" or "Is this agent actually good at X or just good at these specific tests?"</p>

  <h2>Summary Table</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Layer</th><th>Mechanism</th><th>Blocks Export?</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Diversity enforcement</td><td>Jaccard similarity rejection</td><td>No — regenerates</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Intent tracing</td><td>Test to description clause mapping</td><td>No — flags gaps</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Coverage completeness</td><td>CoverageGap alert in ScoreReport</td><td><strong>Yes</strong></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Generalization holdout</td><td>3 unseen shadow tests</td><td>No — warns only</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Audit trail</td><td>Full version + eval history in registry</td><td>No — traceability</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</Layout>
